1. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new approach to hybridize Evolutionary Algorithms with Operational Research methods in the domain of Temporal Planning Problems, which falls under the domain of AI. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - Temporal Planning Problems are often encountered in Robotics, and the proposed approach can be applied to solve such problems. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a memetic scheme that uses local search methods to improve evolutionary solutions, which is a common technique used in machine learning. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new approach to solve complex planning problems by dividing them into smaller sub-problems, which is a common technique used in algorithm design. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The proposed approach can be implemented as a software tool for solving temporal planning problems, which falls under the domain of software engineering.
